gomodel:SYNGO_961  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Dynorphins are agonists of the kappa-opioid receptors. The pro-peptide, called Proenkephalin-B or Preprodynorphin is cleaved into 9 hormone-like peptides, one of which is Dynorphin A (1-8).\nThe paper presents pre-embedding immunoperoxidase-based electron microscopy analysis and shows that Dynorphin A (1-8) is a presynaptic peptide associates with the rims of small SVs (Figure 4-6, very clear in figure 6b) and with the core of large-dense core vesicles.. Experimental description: 'Four adult male Sprague-Dawley rats (Taconic Farms,\nNJ; 200-250 g) were deeply anesthetized with sodium'" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" ;
        dc:date           "2017-07-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_961" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

